    IT.action 0 =ᵐ[𝔓t] fun _ ↦ action0 := by
  exact congrFun (HasLaw.map_eq HasLaw_action_zero_detAlgorithm)
```

This lemma establishes that `IT.action 0` is equal to `fun _ ↦ action0` almost surely with respect to `𝔓t`.

```tactics
lemma action_detAlgorithm_ae_eq [StandardBorelSpace α] [Nonempty α]
    [StandardBorelSpace R] [Nonempty R] (n : ℕ) :
    IT.action (n + 1) =ᵐ[𝔓t] fun h ↦ nextaction n (fun i ↦ h i) := by
  exact congrFun (IT.hasLaw_action_succ _ _).map_eq
```

This lemma establishes that `IT.action (n + 1)` is equal to `fun h ↦ nextaction n (fun i ↦ h i)` almost surely with respect to `𝔓t`.

```tactics
example [StandardBorelSpace α] [Nonempty α]
    [StandardBorelSpace R] [Nonempty R] :
    ∀ᵐ h ∂(𝔓t), IT.action 0 h = action0 ∧
      ∀ n, IT.action (n + 1) h = nextaction n (fun i ↦ h i) := by
  rw [ae_all_iff]
  intro h
  constructor
  · exact h.1
  · intro n
    exact h.2 n
```

This example proves that for all `h` in the support of `𝔓t`, `IT.action 0 h = action0` and `∀ n, IT.action (n + 1) h = nextaction n (fun i ↦ h i)`. This is essentially the definition of the trajectory measure for the deterministic algorithm.

