Now we define the `StreamMeasure` section.

```tactics
section StreamMeasure
```

We define lemmas related to stream measure.

```tactics
lemma _root_.hasLaw_eval_infinitePi {ι : Type*} {X : ι → Type*} {mX : ∀ i, MeasurableSpace (X i)}
  (μ : (i : ι) → Measure (X i)) [hμ : ∀ i, IsProbabilityMeasure (μ i)] (i : ι) :
    HasLaw (Function.eval i) (μ i) (Measure.infinitePi μ) where
  aemeasurable := Measurable.aemeasurable (by fun_prop)
  map_eq := by exact (measurePreserving_eval_infinitePi μ i).map_eq
```

This lemma states that evaluating the infinite product measure `μ` at index `i` gives a measure that is the law of `Function.eval i` with respect to `μ i`.

```tactics
lemma hasLaw_eval_streamMeasure (ν : Kernel α R) [IsMarkovKernel ν] (n : ℕ) :
    HasLaw (fun h : ℕ → α → R ↦ h n) (Measure.infinitePi ν) (Bandit.streamMeasure ν) := by
  apply _root_.hasLaw_eval_infinitePi (fun _ ↦ Measure.infinitePi ν) n
```

This lemma states that the function `fun h : ℕ → α → R ↦ h n` (which evaluates the infinite stream at index `n`) has law `Measure.infinitePi ν` with respect to `Bandit.streamMeasure ν`.

```tactics
lemma hasLaw_eval_eval_streamMeasure (ν : Kernel α R) [IsMarkovKernel ν] (n : ℕ) (a : α) :
    HasLaw (fun h : ℕ → α → R ↦ h n a) (ν a) (Bandit.streamMeasure ν) := by
  (hasLaw_eval_infinitePi ν a).comp (hasLaw_eval_streamMeasure ν n)
```

This lemma states that evaluating the infinite stream at index `n` and then at point `a` has law `ν a` with respect to `Bandit.streamMeasure ν`.

```tactics
lemma identDistrib_eval_eval_id_streamMeasure (ν : Kernel α R) [IsMarkovKernel ν] (n : ℕ) (a : α) :
    IdentDistrib (fun h : ℕ → α → R ↦ h n a) id (Bandit.streamMeasure ν) (ν a) where
  aemeasurable_fst := Measurable.aemeasurable (by fun_prop)
  aemeasurable_snd := Measurable.aemeasurable (by fun_prop)
  map_eq := by
    rw [← (hasLaw_eval_eval_streamMeasure ν n a).map_eq,
      Measure.map_map (by fun_prop) (by fun_prop)]
    simp
```

This lemma proves that the distribution of `fun h : ℕ → α → R ↦ h n a` with respect to `ν a` is the identity distribution. This is needed for the integrability results.

```tactics
lemma Integrable.congr_identDistrib {Ω Ω' : Type*}
    {mΩ : MeasurableSpace Ω} {mΩ' : MeasurableSpace Ω'}
    {μ : Measure Ω} {μ' : Measure Ω'} {X : Ω → ℝ} {Y : Ω' → ℝ}
    (hX : Integrable X μ) (hXY : IdentDistrib X Y μ μ') :
    Integrable Y μ' := by
  have hX' : Integrable id (μ.map X) := by
    rwa [integrable_map_measure (by fun_prop) hXY.aemeasurable_fst]
  rw [hXY.map_eq] at hX'
  rwa [integrable_map_measure (by fun_prop) hXY.aemeasurable_snd] at hX'
```

This lemma states that if `X` is integrable with respect to `μ` and `X` is identically distributed to `Y` with respect to `μ` and `μ'`, then `Y` is integrable with respect to `μ'`.

```tactics
lemma integrable_eval_streamMeasure (ν : Kernel α ℝ) [IsMarkovKernel ν] (n : ℕ) (a : α)
    (h_int : Integrable id (ν a)) :
    Integrable (fun h : ℕ → α → ℝ ↦ h n a) (Bandit.streamMeasure ν) := by
  Integrable.congr_identDistrib h_int (identDistrib_eval_eval_id_streamMeasure ν n a).symm
```

This lemma proves that `fun h : ℕ → α → ℝ ↦ h n a` is integrable with respect to `Bandit.streamMeasure ν` if `id` is integrable with respect to `ν a`.

```tactics
lemma integral_eval_streamMeasure (ν : Kernel α ℝ) [IsMarkovKernel ν] (n : ℕ) (a : α) :
    ∫ h, h n a ∂(Bandit.streamMeasure ν) = (ν a)[id] := by
  calc ∫ h, h n a ∂(Bandit.streamMeasure ν)
  _ = ∫ x, x ∂((Bandit.streamMeasure ν).map (fun h ↦ h n a)) := by
    rw [integral_map (Measurable.aemeasurable (by fun_prop)) (by fun_prop)]
  _ = (ν a)[id] := by simp [(hasLaw_eval_eval_streamMeasure ν n a).map_eq]
```

This lemma calculates the integral of `fun h : ℕ → α → ℝ ↦ h n a` with respect to `Bandit.streamMeasure ν`. The integral is equal to `(ν a)[id]`, which is the expected value of `id` under the measure `ν a`.

```tactics
lemma iIndepFun_eval_streamMeasure' (ν : Kernel α R) [IsMarkovKernel ν] :
    iIndepFun (fun n ω ↦ ω n) (Bandit.streamMeasure ν) := by
  iIndepFun_infinitePi (P := fun (_ : ℕ) ↦ Measure.infinitePi ν) (Ω := fun _ ↦ α → R)
    (X := fun i u ↦ u) (fun i ↦ by fun_prop)
```

This lemma proves that the function `fun n ω ↦ ω n` (which evaluates the infinite stream at index `n`) is independent across indices for the measure `Bandit.streamMeasure ν`.

```tactics
lemma iIndepFun_eval_streamMeasure'' (ν : Kernel α R) [IsMarkovKernel ν] (a : α) :
    iIndepFun (fun n ω ↦ ω n a) (Bandit.streamMeasure ν) := by
  (iIndepFun_eval_streamMeasure' ν).comp (g := fun i ω ↦ ω a) (by fun_prop)
```

This lemma proves that evaluating the infinite stream at index `n` and then at point `a` is independent across indices for the measure `Bandit.streamMeasure ν`.

```tactics
lemma iIndepFun_eval_streamMeasure (ν : Kernel α R) [IsMarkovKernel ν] :
    iIndepFun (fun (p : ℕ × α) ω ↦ ω p.1 p.2) (Bandit.streamMeasure ν) := by
  iIndepFun_uncurry_infinitePi' (X := fun _ _ ↦ id) (fun _ ↦ ν) (by fun_prop)
```

This lemma proves that the function `fun (p : ℕ × α) ω ↦ ω p.1 p.2` (which evaluates the infinite stream at index `p.1` and point `p.2`) is independent across indices for the measure `Bandit.streamMeasure ν`.

```tactics
lemma indepFun_eval_streamMeasure (ν : Kernel α R) [IsMarkovKernel ν] {n m : ℕ} {a b : α}
    (h : n ≠ m ∨ a ≠ b) :
    IndepFun (fun ω ↦ ω n a) (fun ω ↦ ω m b) (Bandit.streamMeasure ν) := by
  change IndepFun (fun ω ↦ ω (n, a).1 (n, a).2) (fun ω ↦ ω (m, b).1 (m, b).2)
    (Bandit.streamMeasure ν)
  exact (iIndepFun_eval_streamMeasure ν).indepFun (by grind)
```

This lemma proves that two functions of the infinite stream are independent. The functions are `fun ω ↦ ω n a` and `fun ω ↦ ω m b`. If `n ≠ m` or `a ≠ b`, these functions are independent.

```tactics
lemma indepFun_eval_streamMeasure' (ν : Kernel α R) [IsMarkovKernel ν] {a b : α} (h : a ≠ b) :
    IndepFun (fun ω n ↦ ω n a) (fun ω n ↦ ω n b) (Bandit.streamMeasure ν) := by
  indepFun_proj_infinitePi_infinitePi h
```

This lemma proves that two functions of the infinite stream are independent. The functions are `fun ω n ↦ ω n a` and `fun ω n ↦ ω n b`. If `a ≠ b`, these functions are independent.

```tactics
lemma indepFun_eval_snd_measure (alg : Algorithm α R) (ν : Kernel α R) [IsMarkovKernel ν]
    {a b : α} (h : a ≠ b) :
    IndepFun (fun ω n ↦ ω.2 n a) (fun ω n ↦ ω.2 n b) (Bandit.measure alg ν) := by
  refine indepFun_snd_prod ?_ ?_ (indepFun_eval_streamMeasure' ν h) (Bandit.trajMeasure alg ν)
  · exact Measurable.aemeasurable (by fun_prop)
  · exact Measurable.aemeasurable (by fun_prop)
```

This lemma proves that two functions of the joint measure are independent. The functions are `fun ω n ↦ ω.2 n a` and `fun ω n ↦ ω.2 n b` (which are the `snd` components of the infinite stream). If `a ≠ b`, these functions are independent.

```tactics
end StreamMeasure
